A vintage-style illustration depicting a complex mechanical relay station from the 1940s era, featuring brass gears, pneumatic tubes, and switching mechanisms passing a single glowing ticket or card through multiple stations. The ticket travels along curved brass rails past different operator stations represented by distinct mechanical arms and sorting mechanisms, each with unique industrial character - some with partner insignias, others with support tools. Warm sepia and copper tones dominate, with art deco geometric patterns in the background. Steam wisps curl around the machinery, and small indicator lights glow amber at each handoff point. The composition shows the ticket mid-journey, creating a sense of purposeful movement through an intricate but orderly system of interconnected parts.
